<div class="racediv" id="aasimar">
  <h2>Aasimar</h2>
  <p>
    Aasimar are the distant descendents of angels and gods. In Elthelas, there are 3 main subgroups of Aasimar, there is the standard Celestial Aasimar, descended
    from angels, planetars, guardinals, or eladrin. There are the descendents of Molton, god of fire and lust, who bears many children with his mortal worshippers.
    Lastly, there are the descendents of the sorceron, who have long since disappeared from the world, but whose mastery over magic lives in in their distant
    descendents.
  </p>
  <h3>Celestial Aasimar</h3> 
  <p>
    Celestial Aasimar are the descendents of the children of unions between good-aligned celestial beings such as angels, planetars, guardinals and eladrin with
    mortal men and women. Celestial Aasimar were once quite common in Elthelas but they have grown increasingly rare in the ages since the God's War, as Celestials
    have largely abandoned Elthelas. Celestials walked the world in that distant age and bred with the various peoples in it. Now Celestial Aasimar mostly appear
    when two families with old Aasimar blood come together.
  </p>
  <h4>D&amp;D 5 Racial Traits</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Ability Score Increase: Your wisdom score increases by 2 and your charisma score increases by 1.
    </li>
    <li>
      Darkvision: 60 ft.
    </li>
    <li>
      6th Sense: Your connection to angelic beings gives you a sense for evil, like an itch at the back of your mind. Whenever someone within 60 ft of you is planning
      an evil deed to happen within the next 10 minutes, you can sense that such thoughts are taking place. However, you cannot tell who is thinking said thoughts or
      what they are planning from this sense alone. You do not need to be able to see or perceive the person thinking those thoughts to get the sense, and you do not
      get these feelings from creatures with an intelligence score of less than 3.
    </li>
    <li>
      Keen senses: You have advantage on perception checks.
    </li>
    <li>
      Godly Connection: You know the light cantrip from the cleric list, and can cast it at will. You also know one first level spell from the cleric list, after you
      cast it, you must complete a short or long rest before you can cast it again. Wisdom is your casting stat for this spell.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Child of Molton</h3>
  <p>
    Molton, God of Fire and Lust, has long made it a habit of dallying with mortal women from among his worshippers. Those willing worshippers whom he selects are
    invited across the planes into his palace, where they report on returning having the best sex of their lives, returning with enough riches to set them and the
    resulting child up for the rest of their lives. His fertility knows no bounds, and even the most infertile women have found themselves with child after such
    encounters. The resulting children are usually still mostly human (and usually female, although not always), but find themselves infused with the essence of
    fire. They are reknowned for their lustful ways(sometimes unfairly) as well as their affinity for fire, music, and dance. Children of Molton look mostly like
    their mothers parentage, but are born with hair in bright fiery colors of red, orange, yellow, blue or green and golden skin. They are also invariably
    beautiful, their skin without unnatural blemishes, faces well balanced, and a form that is lithe and graceful.
  </p>
  <h4>D&amp;D 5 Racial Traits</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Ability Score Increase: Your Dexterity score increases by 2 and your Charisma score increases by 2.</li>
    <li>Size: Children of Molton are generally similar to elves or humans in height, weight, and build. Your size is medium.</li>
    <li>Speed: Your base walking speed is 30 ft.</li>
    <li>Darkvision: You have the darkvision ability up to 120 ft.</li>
    <li>Embodiment of Lust: You have advantage on charisma checks involved in a romantic encounter.</li>
    <li>You have resistance to fire damage.</li>
  </ul>  
  <h3>Sorceron Blooded</h3>
  <p>
    the Sorceron were a race of Godly servants that served all Gods. Originally serving the Gods in creating the world Elthelas and the many interconnecting planes
    of existence in an age long since forgotten. In the Gods War they served on both sides, and were the primary combatants, and while most of them died in that
    conflict, some few survivors retreating to other planes of existence besides the material with the Gods. Yet, before that age many Sorceron interbred with the
    races of Elthelas, and every now and then a child will be born with more Sorceron blood than typical. These unusual children show a rare talent for magic and
    are gifted with intelligence and charisma far beyond that of their kin.
  </p>
