  <div class="racediv" id="elves">
    <h2>Elves</h2>
    <p>
      The elves were the first race to recover after the climactic God's War. The Gods and Sorceron did not see the mostly feral elves of the ancient world as
      reliable soldiers and Sylvan, their patron Goddess went to considerable effort to protect her people from harm. However once the war was over, with the other
      races having highly reduced and scattered populations, the elves finally got around to building cities and expanding. They formed the nation of Eldoran, which
      remains probably the most powerful nation on the planet besides Malinval. However, the high elves have often proven arrogant, and their internal conflicts
      with the moon elves finally resulted in cival war. The Moon Elves successfully asserted their independence and formed the nation of Demal Thor.
    </p>
    <p>
      The Elves are split into 4 distinct subraces, the city dwelling high elves, the rural wood elves, the nomadic moon elves, and the still feral wild elves.
    </p>
    <h3>High Elves</h3>
    <p>
      The High Elves make up the majority of the ruling and merchant class of elves in Eldoran, and are the primary residents in the cities. They are relatively few
      compared to the Wood Elves who live throughout the countryside, but because most elven merchants are high elves, they tend to be considered the most
      stereotypical. High Elves are somewhat weaker, but better educated then Wood Elves.
    </p>
    <h4>D&amp;D 5 Racial Traits</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>Ability Score Increase: Your dexterity score increases by 2 and your intelligence score increases by 1.</li>
      <li>Size: Elves range from under 5 to over 6 feet tall and have slender builds. Your size is medium.</li>
      <li>Speed: Your base walking speed is 30 feet.</li>
      <li>
        Darkvision: Accustomed to twilit forests and the night sky, you have superior vision in dark and dim conditions. You can see in dim light within 60 feet of
        you as if it were bright light, and in darkness as if it were dim light. You can't discern color in the darkness, only shades of gray.
      </li>
      <li>Keen Senses: You have proficiency in the perception skill.</li>
      <li>Fey Ancestry: You have advantage on saving throws against being charmed, and magic can't put you to sleep.</li>
      <li>
        Trance: Elves don't need to sleep. Instead they meditate deeply, remaining semiconscious, for 4 hours a day. (The Common word for such meditation is
        "trance") While meditating, you can dream after a fashion; such dreams are actually mental exercises that have become reflexive through years of practice.
        After resting in this way, you gain the same benefit that a human does from 8 hours of sleep.
      </li>
      <li>Elf Weapon Training: You have proficiency with the longsword, shortsword, shortbow, and longbow.</li>
      <li>Cantrip: You know one cantrip of your choice from the wizard spell list. Intelligence is your spellcasting ability for it.</li>
      <li>Extra Language: You can speak, read, and write one extra language of your choice.</li>
    </ul>
